{"article_id":"mmLJkwf8VISinIHZ","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Kavanaugh Has The Votes","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"To Be Confirmed To The Supreme Court","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"Brett Kavanaugh 's nomination to the Supreme Court cleared a key procedural hurdle in the Senate on Friday ,","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"and his confirmation now seems all but certain ,","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"after a key swing vote , Sen. Susan Collins , R-Maine , declared her support in a speech on the Senate floor .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"Moments after Collins completed her remarks ,","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"Sen. Joe Manchin , D-W.Va. , announced in a statement","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"that he too will support the nomination","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"when it comes up for a final vote .","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"In a much anticipated speech , Collins said","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"that she believed","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"that Christine Blasey Ford ,","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"who accused Kavanaugh of sexually assaulting her","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"when they were both teenagers more than 30 years ago ,","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"was a survivor of sexual assault .","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"Still ,","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"Collins said ,","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"the allegations `` fail to meet the 'more likely than not ' standard , ''","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"and `` I do not believe","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"that these charges can fairly prevent Judge Kavanaugh from serving on the court . ''","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"Speaking to NPR","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"after Collins and Manchin announced their support for Kavanaugh ,","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"a lawyer for Ford addressed","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"whether the California professor feels","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"she failed","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"because confirmation is now a near certainty .","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"`` Dr. Ford 's goal here was never to impact the process","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"to derail a nomination , ''","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"attorney Lisa Banks said on All Things Considered .","depth":6},{"id":29,"text":"`` What she was trying to do was what she thought was the right thing","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"to do as a citizen ,","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"which is to provide the information to the U.S. Senate","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"so they could make the most informed decision possible .","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"Her goal was n't to derail this nomination ,","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"it was to inform the nomination","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"and she 's done that . ''","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"Earlier Friday Collins was part of the majority","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"that voted 51-49","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"to end debate .","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"President Trump tweeted after the procedural vote","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"that he was `` very proud '' of the Senate","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"for taking the critical step .","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"One Democrat , Manchin , voted with Republicans","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"to end debate","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"and move the nomination forward .","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"One Republican , Sen. Lisa Murkowski of Alaska , voted with Democrats against ending debate .","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"In a speech on the Senate floor Saturday night ,","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"hours after the support of Collins and Manchin made it clear","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"Kavanaugh was all but certain to be confirmed ,","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"Murkowski announced","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"she will oppose the nomination","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"when it comes up for a final vote .","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"But as a courtesy to another GOP senator","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"whose daughter is getting married far from D.C. Saturday ,","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"Murkowski also said","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"she will ask","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"that she be recorded as `` present '' in Saturday 's vote .","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"The Alaska Republican noted","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"that being recorded as `` present '' would not change the outcome .","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"In a speech","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"leading up to the vote ,","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"Judiciary Committee Chairman Sen. Chuck Grassley , R-Iowa , said","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"`` the resistance is located right here on Capitol Hill ''","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"and urged his colleagues to `` say no to mob rule ''","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"by voting","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"to confirm Kavanaugh .","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"The top Democrat on the panel , Sen. Dianne Feinstein of California , said","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"Republicans have `` largely chosen to ignore the testimony '' of Ford .","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"Murkowski and Collins sat quietly and undisturbed at their adjacent desks","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"as a clerk called the roll .","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"They sat near the aisle","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"separating senators from both parties","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"- an almost symbolic placement","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"that reflected how the two moderate Republicans were considering crossing the aisle","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"to join with Democratic colleagues","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"to oppose Kavanaugh .","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"Midway through the vote ,","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"as stoic , stone-faced senators sat speechless around them ,","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"Collins and Murkowski began an animated conversation in hushed tones .","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"Both nodded eagerly in agreement with the other .","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"But","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"when all the votes were cast ,","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"ultimately Murkowski voted no","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"and Collins voted yes .","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"It was a surprise to Grassley ,","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"who told reporters","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"he did n't realize","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"the Alaska Republican would vote no","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"until she cast her vote .","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"Trump , in a tweet Friday morning , criticized what he termed `` the very rude elevator screamers , ''","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"who","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"he said","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"are `` paid professionals","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"only looking to make Senators look bad ! ''","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"Without evidence , he alleged","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"that the protesters ,","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"several of whom said","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"they have been sexual assault victims ,","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"were `` paid by [ financier George ] Soros and others . ''","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"Senators had one day to review a confidential supplemental background check into Kavanaugh 's behavior in the early- to mid-1980s","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"when he was in high school and college .","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"The closely guarded collection of interviews is celebrated by Republican leaders as concrete proof","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"that Kavanaugh did not harass or abuse women .","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"Democrats say","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"the interviews ,","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"which they originally requested ,","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"are incomplete and inconclusive .","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"The FBI report did little to alleviate a bitter partisan fight over Kavanaugh 's nomination .","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell , R-Ky. , announced Thursday","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"that the Senate would proceed anyway with the Friday procedural vote .","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"`` What we know for sure","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"is the FBI report did not corroborate any of the allegations against Judge Kavanaugh , ''","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"McConnell said .","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"`` The second thing","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"we know for sure","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"is that there 's no way","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"anything we did","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"would satisfy the Democrats . ''","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"Kavanaugh took an unusual step","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"to boost his nomination","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"Thursday evening ,","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"writing an op-ed in The Wall Street Journal","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"expressing regret for the heated tone of his testimony before the Senate Judiciary Committee last week ,","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"including comments","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"decrying Democratic attacks","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"that were seen by some wavering senators as too partisan .","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"`` I was very emotional last Thursday ,","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"more so","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"than I have ever been .","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"I might have been too emotional at times .","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"I know","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"that my tone was sharp ,","depth":12},{"id":132,"text":"and I said a few things","depth":13},{"id":133,"text":"I should not have said , ''","depth":13},{"id":134,"text":"Kavanaugh wrote .","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"`` Any human being","depth":13},{"id":136,"text":"who has been falsely accused of a range of things","depth":14},{"id":137,"text":"including gang rape","depth":14},{"id":138,"text":"has a right","depth":13},{"id":139,"text":"to be upset ,","depth":13},{"id":140,"text":"has a right","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"to be angry ,","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"and that 's what we saw last week , ''","depth":10},{"id":143,"text":"said White House spokesperson Kerri Kupec during an interview with Morning Edition .","depth":9},{"id":144,"text":"McConnell received the 51 votes","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"needed","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"to clear the procedural hurdle","depth":10},{"id":147,"text":"on Friday .","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"Republicans have enough votes","depth":11},{"id":149,"text":"to ensure Kavanaugh 's nomination in the vote","depth":12},{"id":150,"text":"expected Saturday ,","depth":12},{"id":151,"text":"now that Collins and Manchin have announced their intention","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"to support the judge .","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"Sen. Jeff Flake , R-Ariz. , is a reportedly a yes on the nomination ,","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"barring a major development .","depth":10},{"id":155,"text":"Collins , Murkowski and Flake spent hours in a secure room in the basement of the Capitol on Thursday","depth":13},{"id":156,"text":"reviewing the roughly 45 pages of FBI interviews .","depth":13},{"id":157,"text":"Collins and Flake both said","depth":13},{"id":158,"text":"the investigation was thorough .","depth":13},{"id":159,"text":"Flake forced Republicans to launch the additional investigation last week after a tense negotiation with Senate Judiciary Committee Democrats .","depth":12},{"id":160,"text":"Flake spent a large portion of the afternoon","depth":14},{"id":161,"text":"reviewing the FBI work","depth":14},{"id":162,"text":"and said","depth":14},{"id":163,"text":"he saw no new evidence","depth":16},{"id":164,"text":"to corroborate any of the claims against Kavanaugh ,","depth":16},{"id":165,"text":"which","depth":18},{"id":166,"text":"Flake had previously indicated","depth":18},{"id":167,"text":"would mean","depth":17},{"id":168,"text":"he will vote to confirm .","depth":16},{"id":169,"text":"Democrats saw something very different in the report .","depth":13},{"id":170,"text":"Several criticized Republicans","depth":15},{"id":171,"text":"for limiting the FBI investigation to just nine interviews .","depth":15},{"id":172,"text":"They said","depth":15},{"id":173,"text":"the process ignored many potential witnesses ,","depth":16},{"id":174,"text":"including Ford .","depth":16},{"id":175,"text":"Senate Minority Leader Chuck Schumer , D-N.Y. , said","depth":13},{"id":176,"text":"those issues raised serious doubts about Kavanaugh and his qualifications .","depth":13},{"id":177,"text":"`` Judge Kavanaugh stated at his hearing","depth":12},{"id":178,"text":"that the individuals at the incident","depth":16},{"id":179,"text":"involving Dr. Ford","depth":16},{"id":180,"text":"refuted her version of events , ''","depth":15},{"id":181,"text":"Schumer said Thursday .","depth":14},{"id":182,"text":"`` From their own public statements , we knew that to be false ,","depth":14},{"id":183,"text":"and nothing in this report changes that . ''","depth":14},{"id":184,"text":"Similar concerns moved Sen. Heidi Heitkamp , D-N.D. , to announce Thursday","depth":12},{"id":185,"text":"that she would oppose Kavanaugh .","depth":12},{"id":186,"text":"Heitkamp is one of the most vulnerable Democrats on the ballot in November","depth":14},{"id":187,"text":"and has seen her poll numbers slip in recent weeks .","depth":14},{"id":188,"text":"She is running for re-election in a state","depth":14},{"id":189,"text":"that Trump won in 2016 by more than 35 points .","depth":14},{"id":190,"text":"Heitkamp said","depth":13},{"id":191,"text":"she was troubled by Kavanaugh 's aggressive appearance before the Senate Judiciary Committee and the message","depth":14},{"id":192,"text":"his confirmation would send to women and girls across the country .","depth":14},{"id":193,"text":"`` When considering a lifetime appointment to Supreme Court ,","depth":13},{"id":194,"text":"we must evaluate the totality of the circumstances and record before us , ''","depth":13},{"id":195,"text":"Heitkamp said in a statement .","depth":12},{"id":196,"text":"`` In addition to the concerns about his past conduct , last Thursday 's hearing called into question Judge Kavanaugh 's current temperament , honesty , and impartiality . ''","depth":11}],"relations":[{"parent":393,"left":198,"right":392,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":198,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":392,"left":231,"right":391,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":231,"left":215,"right":230,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":215,"left":204,"right":214,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":204,"left":200,"right":203,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":200,"left":2,"right":199,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":199,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":203,"left":5,"right":202,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":202,"left":6,"right":201,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":201,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":214,"left":209,"right":213,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":209,"left":9,"right":208,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":208,"left":10,"right":207,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":207,"left":206,"right":14,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":206,"left":11,"right":205,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":205,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":213,"left":211,"right":212,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":211,"left":210,"right":17,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":210,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":212,"left":18,"right":19,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":230,"left":220,"right":229,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":220,"left":216,"right":219,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":216,"left":20,"right":21,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"p